  <title translate="true">Method Explorer Summary</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Method Explorer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> allows you to browse (and edit) a list of methods which are related by some criteria. In contrast to the list of methods in the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the methods listed here will typically be from many different classes.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">A new </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Method Explorer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is usually opened by selecting a </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/Definitions Of</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/References To</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/Browse Other</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command in one of the other browsers. Since it does not make sense to open a </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Method Explorer</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> devoid of a context, no icon is provided in the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Folder</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
